INPUT INSTRUCTIONS

  TITLE:	this is an example of a QTL sibling model
  for a continuous outcome using parameter constraints
  DATA:	FILE = ex5.23.dat;
  VARIABLE:	NAMES = y1 y2 pihat;
  	USEVARIABLES = y1 y2;
  	CONSTRAINT = pihat;
  MODEL:	[y1-y2] (1);
  	y1-y2 (var);
  	y1 WITH y2 (cov);
  MODEL CONSTRAINT:
  	NEW(a e q);
  	var = a**2 + e**2 + q**2;
  	cov = 0.5*a**2 + pihat*q**2;



INPUT READING TERMINATED NORMALLY



